Would like to view a release history for any given release.

So when Issues get added to a release or removed from a release a user can easily view a timeline for when these were added and removed, and also provides a convenient view for seeing which issues have been added or removed most recently.

We use a workflow post action to set the Affects Version field in JIRA based on a single select custom field.

The following code worked fine in 3.4

 public void execute(Map transientVars, Map args, PropertySet ps)
    {
		MutableIssue issue = (MutableIssue) transientVars.get("issue");
				String sourceFieldName = "Found in Release";
				CustomField sourceCF = ManagerFactory.getCustomFieldManager().getCustomFieldObjectByName(sourceFieldName);
				if (sourceCF == null) {
					log.error("No custom field '"+sourceFieldName+"' found.");
				}


				Object value = issue.getCustomFieldValue(sourceCF);
				log.debug("Setting affects version to " + value );
				
				issue.setAffectedVersions(EasyList.build(value));
				
			}

because the custom field single value picker returned a VersionImpl

Now in 3.5, the getCustomFieldValue returns a Collection of 1.

I'm not sure I want/need this fixed now (in fact it would break my update), but just in case others encounter this

